a%20better%20look%20at%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22image%20of%20ship%20on%20screen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657cc9707a3c8094d5ddc2d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20sunken%20ship%20as%20it%20appeared%20on%20Wollak's%20screen.%3Cp%3ETim%20Wollak%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20the%20object%20appeared%20on%20the%20small%20device's%20screen%20made%20his%20daughter%20Henley%20(who%20loves%20The%20Little%20Mermaid)%20think%20it%20was%20an%20octopus%2C%20Wollak%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Wollak%20noticed%20the%20wooden%20panels%20that%20almost%20looked%20%26quot%3Blike%20a%20human%20ribcage%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20immediately%20assumed%20it%20was%20some%20kind%20of%20sunken%20boat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22sonar%20image%20of%20wooden%20wreck%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657ccaa47a3c8094d5ddc380%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESonar%20image%20of%20the%20wreck%20taken%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Natural%20Resources.%3Cp%3EWisconsin%20Department%20of%20Natural%20Resources%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20be%20honest%2C%26quot%3B%20Wollak%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20saw%20it%2C%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20cool.%20But%20we%20were%20in%20an%20area%20where%20people%20go%20all%20the%20time%2C%20and%20so%20I%20just%20assumed%20that%20people%20knew%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20took%20a%20couple%20pictures%2C%20sent%20'em%20some%20buddies%20to%20see%20if%20they%20knew%20about%20it%2C%20which%20they%20didn't%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20looked%20at%20it%20and%20then%20we%20drove%20off%20and%20went%20to%20look%20for%20fish%20somewhere%20else.%20We%20didn't%20really%20think%20a%20whole%20ton%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20several%20months%20later%20that%20Wollak%20learned%20the%20significance%20of%20his%20discovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWollak%20posted%20about%20his%20find%20on%20a%20local%20Facebook%20page%20called%20Forgotten%20Wisconsin%20a%20few%20months%20later%2C%20writing%20that%20he%20believed%20it%20was%20the%20wreck%20of%20a%20ship%20called%20the%20Erie%20L.%20Hackley.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20within%20an%20hour%20of%20his%20post%2C%20he%20said%2C%20someone%20from%20the%20Wisconsin%20Historical%20Society%20reached%20out%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Historical%20Society%20told%20him%20they%20didn't%20believe%20it%20could%20be%20the%20Hackley%2C%20based%20on%20its%20location.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Wollak%20said%2C%20they%20thought%20it%20was%20likely%20the%201871%20wreck%20of%20a%20barkentine%20ship%20called%20the%20George%20L.%20Newman%2C%20which%20was%20thought%20to%20have%20sunk%20in%20that%20area%20but%20had%20never%20been%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Wisconsin%20Department%20of%20Natural%20Resources%20gathered%20video%20footage%20on%20the%20wreck%20earlier%20this%20month%3B%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20wreck%20hasn't%20been%20fully%20confirmed%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fwisconsinhistoricalsociety%2Fposts%2Fpfbid02WwPCPXQBZJ6DjMa3zRqnAEECsRDYSZisJfnRKh6xZaEn8n6Wwq2ZXchrMi44NXyHl%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Wisconsin%20Historical%20Society%20wrote%20in%20a%20Facebook%20post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221856%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22image%20of%20wooden%20boat%20planks%20underwater%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657cca5c0ec98e92f75035f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20still%20image%20from%20the%20ROV%20footage%20of%20the%20George%20L.%20Newman%20taken%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Natural%20Resources.%3Cp%3EWisconsin%20Department%20of%20Natural%20Resources%3C%2F