20the%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fmeghanmakesmoney%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeghan%20Lim%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20North%20Carolina%20said%20she's%20been%20doing%20pet%20sitting%20as%20a%20side%20hustle%20for%20a%20few%20years%20now%2C%20starting%20when%20she%20was%20in%20college.%20She's%20now%20a%20financial%20analyst%20and%20still%20makes%20extra%20money%20through%20pet%20sitting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20Meghan%20Lim%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b6a150ec98e92f74fa927%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMeghan%20Lim.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Meghan%20Lim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she's%20done%20pet%20sitting%20through%20apps%2C%20but%20she%20now%20does%20it%20privately%20too.%20Working%20privately%20means%20clients%20can%20pay%20her%20directly%20and%20can%20avoid%20service%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELim%20said%20she%20has%20raised%20her%20rates%20since%20she%20first%20started.%20She%20said%20she%20thinks%20many%20of%20her%20higher-income%20clients%20are%20%26quot%3Bwilling%20to%20pay%20a%20premium%20for%20their%20pets%20to%20be%20taken%20care%20of.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20can%20house%20sit%20while%20taking%20care%20of%20pets%2C%20which%20she%20says%20tends%20to%20pay%20more%20than%20just%20dog%20walking.%20While%20this%20can%20include%20walking%20dogs%20too%2C%20house%20sitting%20can%20also%20mean%20giving%20necessary%20medication%2C%20feeding%20the%20pet%20or%20pets%2C%20and%20giving%20them%20attention%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20stay%20overnight%2C%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20my%20time%20with%20the%20dog%2C%20and%20because%20I%20work%20remotely%2C%20it%20helps%20that%20I%20can%20bring%20my%20laptop%20wherever%20I%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20Lim%20said.%20%26quot%3BPet%20sitting%20kind%20of%20feels%20like%20a%20free%20Airbnb%20but%20with%20a%20dog.%20But%20you're%20also%20getting%20paid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20noted%20overnight%20stays%20could%20typically%20earn%20her%20between%20%24100%20to%20%24150%20a%20night%20but%20it%20really%20varies%20given%20the%20number%20of%20dogs%20or%20cats%20she's%20watching%20and%20if%20it's%20the%20holidays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20can%20typically%20make%20around%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20from%20dog%20walking%2C%20drop%20in%20visits%2C%20and%20pet%20sitting.%20She%20suggested%20to%20people%20starting%20pet%20sitting%20starting%20with%20%2450%20to%20%2460%20a%20night%20as%20their%20rate%2C%20but%20she%20also%20suggested%20to%20check%20other%20rates%20where%20they%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEspecially%20during%20the%20holiday%20season%2C%20it's%20nice%20because%20if%20you're%20not%20spending%20it%20with%20family%2C%20you%20could%20charge%20extra%20as%20a%20pet%20sitter%2C%26quot%3B%20Lim%20said%2C%20noting%20that%20people%20may%20be%20looking%20for%20this%20if%20they%20are%20going%20out%20of%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYou%20can%20make%20content%20about%20products%20or%20to%20market%20another%20side%20gig%20you%20have%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELim%20has%20also%20done%20content%20creation%20as%20a%20side%20hustle.%20She%20thinks%20it's%20%26quot%3Ba%20super%20lucrative%20side%20hustle%20that%20anyone%20can%20get%20into%26quot%3B%20but%20notes%20it%20does%20take%20time%20and%20effort%20to%20do%20things%20like%20editing%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she's%20been%20doing%20it%20consistently%20for%20a%20few%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELim%20also%20recently%20started%20selling%20a%20budget%20template%20she%20made%20for%20people%20trying%20to%20get%20their%20finances%20in%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20released%20my%20template%2C%20I%20put%20it%20on%20sale%20for%20%245%2C%20and%20I%20basically%20marketed%20it%20to%20look%20like%2C%20'Hey%2C%20instead%20of%20shopping%20for%20Black%20Friday%2C%20why%20not%20get%20this%20template%20to%20help%20you%20fix%20your%20finances%20for%20the%20new%20year%3F'%20And%20so%20I've%20been%20generating%20a%20lot%20of%20sales%20from%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Lim%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20three%20weeks%20since%20she%20started%20selling%20the%20template%2C%20she's%20already%20made%20a%20net%20figure%20of%20%241%2C900%20off%20over%20200%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20she%20offers%20one-on-one%20coaching%20%26quot%3Bwith%20people%20who%20need%20some%20more%20help%20with%20their%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELim%20suggested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuser-generated-content-creator-make-thousands-per-month-social-media-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Euser-generated%20content%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20good%20side%20hustle%20to%20try%20during%20the%20holidays%20given%20anyone%20can%20get%20into%20it%20and%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20have%20a%20following%20to%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20want%20regular%20people%20to%20make%20videos%20about%20their%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20Lim%20said.%20%26quot%3BAround%20the%20holidays%20people%20are%20shopping%20and%20people%20want%20to%20push%20out%20their%20products%20a%20lot%20during%20Black%20Friday%2C%20Christmas%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELim%20made%20hundreds%20of%20dollars%20for%20a%20few%20short%20user-generated%20content%20videos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYou%20can%20also%20try%20delivery%20apps%20or%20the%20Amazon%20Influencer%20Program%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%2C%20who%20makes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40sidehustlereview%3Flang%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideos%20evaluating%20different%20side%20hustles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20retail%20delivery%20apps%20are%20good%20holiday%20hustles%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Egiven%20the%20demand%20for%20these%20services.%20Ryan%20said%20they%20can%20offer%20incentives%2C%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20them%20an%20excellent%20choice%20for%20those%20looking%20to%20earn%20quickly%2C%20especially%20to%20fund%20holiday%20expenses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221471%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20Ryan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b6a6550edbc52a8646d7a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221103%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERyan.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Ryan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20thinks%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate-program.amazon.com%2Finfluencers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20Influencer%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecould%20also%20be%20a%20good%20option%20to%20make%20money%20during%20the%20holiday%20period%20given%20Amazon's%20traffic%20during%20this%20time.%20Ryan%20said%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20the%20'on-site%20commission'%20feature%20unlocked%20can%20be%20highly%20lucrative.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20the%20payment%20process%20includes%20a%2060-day%20holding%20period%2C%20meaning%20the%20earnings%20are%20available%20post-holidays%2C%20the%20potential%20for%20substantial%20revenue%20is%20significant%2C%26quot%3B%20Ryan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20had%20success%20with%20trying%20side%20hustles%20over%20the%20holiday%20season%20or%20throughout%20the%20year%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20report%20to%20share%20your%20story%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-airbnb-ugc-pets-selling-items-extra-money-holidays-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702812181000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b67d17a3c8094d5dd2e18%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-airbnb-ugc-pets-selling-items-extra-money-holidays-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hosting%20on%20Airbnb%2C%20pet%20sitting%2C%20and%20babysitting%20are%20three%20side%20hustles%20to%20try%20this%20holiday%20season%20to%20make%20some%20extra%20money.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-airbnb-ugc-pets-selling-items-extra-money-holidays-2023-12%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20long%2C%20brutal%20reign%20of%20Wall%20Street's%20private-equity%20kings%20is%20over%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20business%20man%20in%20a%20coffin%20with%20money%20floating%20away%20from%20him%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657ca8647a3c8094d5dda7f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPrivate%20equity%20saw%20a%20decade-long%20boom%2C%20but%20in%20recent%20years%20both%20the%20market%20and%20American%20society%20have%20turned%20on%20Wall%20Street's%20buyout%20kings.%3Cp%3EiStock%3B%20Rebecca%20Zisser%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Wall%20Street%20money%20managers%20fall%20from%20grace%2C%20there's%20usually%20some%20kind%20of%20discernible%20ruckus%3A%20the%20wail%20of%20angry%20investors%2C%20the%20steady%20drone%20of%20thousands%20of%20lawyers%20filing%20cases%2C%20and%20the%20rush%20of%20doomer%20headlines%20in%20the%20financial%20press.%20But%20even%20as%20some%20of%20Wall%20Street's%20elite%20are%20getting%20decimated%2C%20you%20can%20barely%20hear%20a%20sound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20post-financial-crisis%20world%20of%20zero%20interest%20rates%2C%20private%20equity%20%E2%80%94%20a%20clubby%20world%20of%20investment%20firms%20that%20use%20leverage%20(as%20well%20as%20some%20equity)%20to%20purchase%20portfolio%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20places%20on%20Wall%20Street%20that%20guaranteed%20investors%20yield.%20But%20after%20that%20decade%20of%20winning%2C%20the%20industry's%20fortunes%20have%20started%20to%20turn%20%E2%80%94%20though%20you%20probably%20won't%20hear%20too%20much%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20relative%20silence%20is%20because%20of%20the%20nature%20of%20private%20equity%20itself.%20Client%20funds%20are%20locked%20in%2C%20investments%20are%20rather%20hush-hush%2C%20and%20standard%20fee%20structures%20ensure%20that%20the%20rich%20stay%20rich%20regardless%20of%20how%20markets%20move.%20Under%20that%20blanket%20of%20protection%2C%20though%2C%20you%20might%20hear%20some%20muffled%20screams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20both%20the%20market%20and%20American%20society%20have%20turned%20on%20private%20equity.%20Rising%20interest%20rates%20have%20thrown%20a%20wrench%20in%20PE's%20debt-laden%20business%20model.%20Meanwhile%2C%20regulators%20are%20starting%20to%20view%20PE's%20practices%20as%20anticompetitive%20and%20antisocial.%20%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20post-COVID%2C%20pro-reshoring%20world%2C%20PE's%20ethos%20of%20efficiency%20is%20giving%20way%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3Ereclamation%20of%20the%20redundant%20%E2%80%94%20a%20recognition%20that%20even%20if%20it's%20more%20expensive%2C%20having%20extra%20capacity%20in%20the%20economy%20benefits%20competition%2C%20public%20health%2C%20and%20national%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELook%2C%20I'm%20not%20saying%20that%20the%20private-equity%20section%20of%20the%20billionaire%20boys'%20club%20is%20about%20to%20empty%20out%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20saying%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20a%20few%20messy%20years.%20We're%20going%20to%20see%20companies%20blow%20up%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20see%20balance%20sheets%20get%20strained%2C%20and%20in%20that%20chaos%2C%20we're%20going%20to%20see%20a%20whole%20bunch%20of%20money%20get%20flushed%20down%20the%20drain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EEven%20the%20biggest%20and%20best%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EPE%20has%20made%20it%20rain%20for%20so%20long%20because%20its%20most%20common%20playbook%20is%20based%20on%20debt.%20First%2C%20a%20private-equity%20firm%20raises%20money%20for%20a%20fund%20using%20some%20of%20its%20own%20capital%20and%20some%20from%20outside%20investors.%20Second%2C%20the%20firm%20finds%20a%20business%20they%20think%20is%20underperforming%20or%20in%20a%20weak%20position%20and%20gobbles%20it%20up.%20But!%20Instead%20of%20blowing%20through%20all%20of%20the%20fund's%20cash%20upfront%2C%20the%20PE%20firm%20uses%20a%20sliver%20of%20that%20cash%20to%20invest%20in%20the%20firm%20and%20takes%20out%20a%20loan%20on%20the%20company's%20behalf%20to%20cover%20the%20rest.%20Then%20the%20investors%20dump%20all%20of%20that%20debt%20onto%20the%20company's%20balance%20sheet%2C%20a%20move%20called%20a%20leveraged%20buyout.%20After%20that%2C%20the%20firm%20gets%20to%20work%20trying%20to%20strengthen%20the%20company%2C%20maybe%20through%20layoffs%20or%20maybe%20by%20making%20internal%20processes%20more%20efficient.%20Once%20the%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Bright-sized%26quot%3B%20and%20making%20enough%20to%20start%20paying%20off%20the%20debt%2C%20the%20PE%20firm%20flips%20the%20company%2C%20either%20by%20taking%20it%20back%20to%20the%20public%20markets%20via%20an%20IPO%20or%20selling%20it%20to%20another%20party%20%E2%80%94%20a%20competitor%2C%20a%20conglomerate%2C%20what%20have%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20years%20following%20the%20financial%20crisis%20were%20perfect%20for%20this%20kind%20of%20play.%20Because%20interest%20rates%20around%20the%20world%20were%20at%20zero%2C%20it%20was%20easy%20to%20take%20out%20a%20loan%20and%20cheap%20to%20manage%20all%20that%20debt.%20Investors%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20especially%20the%20large%20institutional%20ones%20like%20pension%20funds%2C%20had%20limited%20options%20for%20fat%20returns%20in%20a%20world%20where%20once-safe%20bonds%20yielded%20so%20little.%20So%20they%20were%20willing%20to%20dive%20headfirst%20into%20anything%20that%20promised%20them%20higher-than-average%20returns.%20By%202022%2C%20the%20American%20Investment%20Council%20reported%20that%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investmentcouncil.org%2Fprivate-equity-delivers-the-strongest-returns-for-public-servants%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-in-10%20US%20pension%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20invested%20in%20private%20equity.%20Back%20in%202006%2C%20alternative%20investments%20%E2%80%94%20money%20put%20toward%20private%20equity%2C%20hedge%20funds%2C%20and%20distressed%20real-estate%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20made%20up%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdigitalcommons.law.umaryland.edu%2Fcgi%2Fviewcontent.cgi%3Farticle%3D3931%26context%3Dmlr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E11%25%20of%20public%20pension%20fund's%20portfolios%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20by%202016%20that%20number%20had%20hit%2026%25.%20By%202021%2C%20the%20last%20year%20of%20the%20golden%20times%2C%20PE%20did%20a%20record%20%241.2%20trillion%20worth%20of%20deals%2C%20according%20to%20PitchBook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20started%20hiking%20interest%20rates%2C%20fortunes%20changed%20in%20kind.%20Taking%20out%20a%20loan%20has%20become%20more%20expensive%2C%20drastically%20changing%20the%20rationality%20of%20private%20equity's%20business%20model.%20Leveraged%20buyouts%20suddenly%20look%20stupid%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fmarkets%2Fglobal-markets-private-equity-graphic-2023-06-26%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPE%20dealmaking%20drastically%20decelerated%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20where%20it%20sits%20now%2C%20at%20a%20four-year%20low%20and%20well%20below%20pre-pandemic%20levels.%20Along%20with%20fewer%20deals%2C%20PE%20firms%20have%20also%20been%20forced%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20(potentially)%20debt-laden%20companies%20for%20longer.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fmarketintelligence%2Fen%2Fnews-insights%2Flatest-news-headlines%2Fprivate-equity-buyout-funds-show-longest-holding-periods-in-2-decades-79033309%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaverage%20holding%20period%20for%20US%20and%20Canadian%20buyout%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20risen%20to%207.3%20years%20in%202023%2C%20the%20longest%20hold%20time%20since%202000%2C%20according%20to%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%20Market%20Intelligence.%20Other%20signs%20of%20this%20pain%20are%20everywhere%3A%20The%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.spglobal.com%2Fmarketintelligence%2Fen%2Fnews-insights%2Flatest-news-headlines%2Fprivate-equity-fund-launches-pacing-for-big-decline-after-paltry-h1-76517923%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20PE%20funds%20being%20launched%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20fallen%20off%20a%20cliff%2C%20and%20making%20matters%20worse%20for%20PE%2C%20bonds%20are%20back%2C%20baby.%20For%20investors%2C%20why%20give%20all%20your%20millions%20to%20private-equity%20firms%20to%20take%20on%20risk%20when%20safe%2C%20investment-grade%20bonds%20are%20yielding%20mid-single%20digits%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20biggest%20players%20have%20various%20reasons%20to%20worry.%20Over%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fearnings%2Fcarlyle-group-posts-lower-3q-revenue-218fdfcf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECarlyle%20Group%2C%20distributable%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20profits%20that%20can%20be%20returned%20to%20shareholders%20%E2%80%94%20fell%20to%20%24367.4%20million%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20down%2043%25%20from%20the%20same%20time%20last%20year.%20At%20KKR%2C%20distributable%20earnings%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20were%20down%206.6%25%20compared%20to%20the%20same%20time%20the%20year%20before%2C%20much%20better%20than%20the%2023%25%20year-on-year%20drop%20the%20firm%20reported%20in%20the%20second%20quarter.%20This%20summer%2C%20the%20ratings%20agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.crainsnewyork.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate%2Fmoodys-downgrades-blackstone-kkr-apollo-real-estate-funds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMoody's%20downgraded%3C%2Fa%3E%20Blackstone%2C%20Apollo%2C%20and%20KKR%20because%20of%20their%20large%20commercial%20real-estate%20holdings%20(only%2066%25%20of%20US%20workers%20have%20returned%20to%20the%20office%20full%20time%2C%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fowllabs.com%2Fstate-of-hybrid-work%2F2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20indicate).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20we%20are%20at%20a%20point%20in%20time%20when%20PE%20is%20starting%20to%20lose%20the%20differential%2C%20the%20alpha%2C%20where%20they%20are%20making%20more%20money%20than%20other%20investments%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Pulitzer%20Prize-winning%20journalist%20Gretchen%20Morgenson%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthedig.substack.com%2Fp%2Fmorgenson-and-rosner-talk-about-plunderous%3Futm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%23media-f1f7af08-4466-43ef-a66e-536e3d51ced2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20interview%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20her%20book%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D000111d950d9db963e086ae6d70c28a030fb9fa6db01fccf02999c28327bfba9%26postID%3D65788fc64c878294df249cf3%26postSlug%3Dwall-street-private-equity-woes-debt-stock-market-interest-rates-2023-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.amazon.com%252FThese-Are-Plunderers-Runs_and-Wrecks_America%252Fdp%252F1982191287%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThese%20Are%20the%20Plunderers%3A%20How%20Private%20Equity%20Runs%20%E2%80%95%20and%20Wrecks%20%E2%80%95%20America%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivate-equity%20firms%20were%20able%20to%20hide%20these%20troubles%20for%20a%20while%2C%20thanks%20in%20large%20part%20to%20the%20way%20they%20structure%20their%20investment%20vehicles.%20Morgenson%20and%20her%20coauthor%2C%20Joshua%20Rosner%2C%20argue%20that%20PE's%20proprietary%20way%20of%20marking%20the%20value%20of%20their%20investments%20has%20been%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20on%20paper%20%E2%80%94%20providing%20the%20industry%20with%20exaggerated%20returns%20compared%20to%20public%20companies.%20Publicly%20traded%20companies%20must%20disclose%20financial%20information%2C%20but%20PE%20acquisitions%20are%20privately%20held.%20That%20opacity%20has%20given%20PE%20an%20opportunity%20for%20what%20Morgenson%20called%20%26quot%3Bwiggle%20room%20%E2%80%A6%20if%20not%20outright%20lying%20about%20what%20the%20performance%20numbers%20are.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20denying%20that%20in%20the%20face%20of%20higher%20interest%20rates%2C%20some%20in%20the%20industry%20are%20engaging%20in%20a%20bit%20of%20sleight%20of%20hand.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F8b4a5df6-7f6d-480f-8d20-55793854c37e%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReporters%20at%20the%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20together%20an%20excellent%20rundown%20of%20the%20kind%20of%20financial%20contortions%20money%20managers%20are%20using%20these%20days%3A%20holding%20on%20to%20good%20assets%20and%20moving%20them%20into%20funds%20with%20poorly%20performing%20assets%3B%20deferring%20interest%20payments%20for%20debt-laden%20companies%20and%20instead%20adding%20them%20to%20the%20overall%20debt%20pile%20to%20be%20paid%20at%20some%20later%20date%3B%20collateralizing%20good%20assets%20to%20pay%20off%20debt%20for%20failing%20ones.%20Obviously%2C%20none%20of%20these%20are%20permanent%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20time%20passes%2C%20the%20more%20money%20PE%20firms%20need%20to%20spend%20to%20hold%20their%20portfolio%20companies%2C%20and%20the%20harder%20it%20gets%20to%20juggle%20all%20this.%20Conditions%20will%20improve%20for%20private%20equity%20when%20interest%20rates%20go%20down.%20Until%20then%2C%20and%20perhaps%20even%20after%20that%2C%20expect%20the%20internal%20asset%20churn%20to%20continue%20until%20some%20firms%20quietly%20shutter%20or%20turn%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2023-09-24%2Fprivate-equity-zombie-firms-leave-pension-funds-with-hard-choices%3Fembedded-checkout%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ezombie%20firms%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20sucking%20up%20fees%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20stagnating%20companies%20while%20too-patient%20investors%20get%20stuck%20holding%20the%20bag.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFrom%20go-go%20to%20get%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20decades%2C%20private-equity%20firms%20have%20made%20it%20their%20mission%20to%20right-size%20US%20corporations%3A%20compelling%20companies%20that%20investment%20managers%20deem%20%26quot%3Bunderperforming%26quot%3B%20to%20lay%20off%20workers%2C%20sell%20assets%2C%20and%20slash%20costs%2C%20even%20if%20it%20meant%20a%20worse%20product%20for%20the%20end%20consumer.%20So%20it's%20somewhat%20ironic%20that%20US%20policymakers%20are%20starting%20to%20wonder%20if%20it's%20the%20PE%20industry%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20right-sized.%20It%20was%20one%20thing%20when%20PE%20was%20seeking%20to%20squeeze%20out%20efficiencies%20from%20bloated%20industrial%20conglomerates%20or%20moribund%20IT%20firms%2C%20but%20over%20the%20past%20decade-plus%2C%20the%20tentacles%20of%20private%20equity%20have%20spread%20to%20a%20wider%20range%20of%20industries%20%E2%80%94%20from%20HVAC%20repair%20and%20higher%20education%20to%20nursing%20homes%20and%20hospitals.%20It's%20become%20clear%20that%20the%20efficiency-obsessed%20tactics%20are%20hurting%20consumers%20and%20leaving%20our%20most%20vulnerable%20members%20of%20society%20in%20the%20lurch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet's%20take%20higher%20education%2C%20for%20example.%20It's%20an%20industry%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20government%20subsidies%2C%20and%20private-equity%20firms%20have%20been%20able%20to%20acquire%20hundreds%20of%20for-profit%20schools%20and%20capture%20those%20subsidies%20for%20their%20investors.%20The%20problem%2C%20according%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw24976%2Frevisions%2Fw24976.rev0.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20to%20a%202018%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20researchers%20at%20NYU's%20Stern%20School%20of%20Business%2C%20is%20that%20the%20students%20get%20shortchanged%20out%20of%20a%20quality%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20study%20of%2088%20private-equity%20deals%20and%20994%20schools%20under%20PE%20ownership%2C%20the%20researchers%20concluded%20that%20%26quot%3Bprivate%20equity%20buyouts%20lead%20to%20higher%20enrollment%20and%20profits%2C%20but%20also%20to%20lower%20education%20inputs%2C%20higher%20tuition%2C%20higher%20per-student%20debt%2C%20lower%20graduation%20rates%2C%20lower%20student%20loan%20repayment%20rates%2C%20and%20lower%20earnings%20among%20graduates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20the%20same%20story%20at%20nursing%20homes.%20A%20study%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fdigest%2F202104%2Fhow-patients-fare-when-private-equity-funds-acquire-nursing-homes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20PE-owned%20nursing%20homes%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20understaffed%2C%20pay%20higher%20management%20fees%2C%20charge%20patients%20more%2C%20and%20have%20higher%20patient-mortality%20rates.%20%26quot%3BPatients%20admitted%20to%20private%20equity-owned%20nursing%20homes%20are%2050%25%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20placed%20on%20antipsychotic%20medication.%20By%20sedating%20patients%20rather%20than%20applying%20behavioral%20therapy%2C%20nursing%20homes%20can%20reduce%20staffing%20needs.%20Private%20equity-owned%20homes%20also%20perform%20below%20average%20in%20two%20other%20key%20metrics%20of%20well-being%3A%20patients%20experience%20a%20greater%20decline%20in%20mobility%20and%20increased%20levels%20of%20pain%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20paper%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Congress%20passed%20the%20No%20Surprises%20Act%2C%20to%20stop%20hospitals%20from%20charging%20patients%20unexpected%2C%20eye-popping%20bills%20after%20visits%20to%20the%20emergency%20room.%20Private-equity-owned%20hospitals%20were%20the%20driving%20force%20behind%20those%20surprise%20charges%2C%20and%20they%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F09%2F13%2Fupshot%2Fsurprise-billing-laws-ad-spending-doctor-patient-unity.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20fought%20as%20hard%20as%20they%20could%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20keep%20the%20bill%20from%20passing.%20Researchers%20estimate%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Frobertpearl%2F2023%2F02%2F20%2Fprivate-equity-and-the-monopolization-of-medical-care%2F%3Fsh%3D73caf0542bad%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E25%25%20to%2040%25%20of%20emergency%20rooms%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20run%20by%20PE%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20trends%20we've%20seen%20over%20the%20last%20decade%20is%20greater%20expansion%20of%20PE%20in%20healthcare%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20Lina%20Khan%2C%20the%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%20chair%2C%20said%20on%20a%20recent%20episode%20of%20the%20Bloomberg%20podcast%20%26quot%3BOdd%20Lots.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BAt%20the%20FTC%2C%20we%20are%20business-model%20agnostic%2C%20but%20we%20have%20been%20hearing%20from%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20market%20participants%2C%20including%20healthcare%20workers%2C%20about%20the%20ways%20in%20which%20PE's%20incursion%20can%20result%20in%20detrimental%20outcomes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20practice%20Khan%20is%20specifically%20concerned%20about%20is%20called%20a%20roll-up%20%E2%80%94%20in%20which%20a%20PE%20firm%20buys%20up%20all%20the%20small%20businesses%20in%20an%20area%20that%20are%20focused%20on%20the%20same%20type%20of%20service%20and%20merges%20them.%20In%20theory%2C%20this%20sort%20of%20consolidation%20is%20supposed%20to%20make%20operations%20more%20efficient%20by%20combining%20resources%20to%20lower%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20mention%20net%20the%20investors%20a%20tidy%20profit.%20But%20in%20reality%2C%20it%20creates%20a%20monopoly%20that%20is%20able%20to%20control%20prices.%20The%20FTC%20recently%20brought%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20a%20Texas-based%20company%2C%20US%20Anesthesia%20Partners%2C%20and%20the%20private-equity%20firm%20Welsh%2C%20Carson%2C%20Anderson%20%26amp%3B%20Stowe%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%20a%20scheme%20to%20buy%20up%20all%20of%20Texas'%20largest%20anesthesiology%20practices%20in%20order%20to%20jack%20up%20prices.%20%26quot%3BThis%20action%20puts%20the%20market%20on%20notice%20that%20we%20will%20scrutinize%20roll-up%20schemes%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Flina-khan-speaks-ftc-private-152058844.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKhan%20said.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%2C%20this%20isn't%20to%20say%20that%20all%20PE%20firms%20are%20out%20to%20do%20evil%2C%20but%20their%20business%20model%20has%20clear%20limits.%20If%20the%20pandemic%20taught%20us%20anything%2C%20it%20is%20that%20efficiency%20isn't%20everything%2C%20nor%20should%20it%20be%20in%20all%20cases.%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20certain%20sectors%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20it's%20in%20the%20public%20interest%20to%20allow%20humanity%20to%20supersede%20the%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wish%20I%20could%20tell%20you%20that%20someone%2C%20somewhere%20was%20working%20on%20changing%20the%20private-equity%20game%20so%20that%20risk%20is%20more%20equitably%20distributed%20throughout%20the%20process.%20There%20are%20some%20in%20Washington%2C%20like%20Sen.%20Elizabeth%20Warren%2C%20who%20want%20to%20pass%20legislation%20that%20would%20force%20PE%20companies%20to%20wait%20two%20years%20before%20using%20the%20debt%20on%20acquisition%20companies%20to%20pay%20out%20dividends%20to%20investors.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20Democrats%20and%20some%20Republicans%20have%20agreed%20for%20years%20that%20it's%20time%20to%20close%20the%20carried-interest%20loophole%20%E2%80%94%20a%20rule%20that%20allows%20investment-fund%20gains%20to%20be%20taxed%20at%20a%20lower%20rate%20and%20largely%20benefits%20PE%20firms%20and%20hedge%20funds.%20And%20yet%2C%20it%20somehow%20never%20gets%20done.%20Both%20of%20these%20practices%20help%20keep%20the%20industry%20humming%20along%2C%20even%20as%20investments%20fail.%20That%20is%20why%20all%20of%20this%20money%20is%20dissipating%20so%20soundlessly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20private-equity%20firm%20invests%20in%20a%20business%2C%20it%20often%20streamlines%20operations%20down%20to%20the%20last%20penny.%20But%20if%20the%20past%20decade%20or%20so%20has%20shown%20us%20anything%20about%20the%20industry%2C%20it's%20how%20to%20succeed%20with%20excess%20%E2%80%94%20an%20excess%20of%20capital%2C%20an%20excess%20of%20leverage%2C%20and%20an%20excess%20of%20opportunities.%20We're%20about%20to%20find%20out%20if%20the%20industry%20can%20survive%20without%20it%2C%20or%20if%20it%20was%20really%20excess%20keeping%20the%20kings%20of%20efficiency%20fat%20and%20happy%20all%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Flinette-lopez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELinette%20Lopez%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-private-equity-woes-debt-stock-market-interest-rates-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702812121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657ca84e0ec98e92f75019ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-private-equity-woes-debt-stock-market-interest-rates-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Private%20equity%20giants%20spent%20years%20buying%20up%20vulnerable%20companies%20and%20stripping%20them%20for%20parts.%20Now%20it's%20coming%20back%20to%20haunt%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22llopez%40insider.com%20(Linette%20Lopez)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canoni