be%20able%20to%20do%20things%20that%20we%20never%20thought%20were%20possible.%20And%20we're%20going%20to%20start%20to%20see%20the%20separation%20between%20vision%20and%20what's%20really%20available%20right%20now%20today.%20I%20think%20we're%20going%20to%20be%20amazed%20by%20what%20new%20capabilities%20are%20going%20to%20be%20at%20our%20disposal.%20I%20think%20AI%20is%20going%20to%20be%20very%20exciting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20your%20biggest%20concern%20for%202024%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20to%20start%20with%20just%20the%20nature%20of%20what's%20going%20on%20around%20the%20world%20with%20global%20conflicts.%20We%20have%20employees%20in%20Europe.%20We%20have%20employees%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20in%20Israel%20specifically.%20We%20have%20many%20members%20of%20our%20team%20that%20have%20relationships%20with%20people%20that%20are%20also%20being%20impacted%20directly%20%E2%80%94%20family%20members%2C%20friends%20%E2%80%94%20by%20these%20conflicts.%20That's%20something%20I'm%20definitely%20personally%20concerned%20about%3A%20the%20continuation%20of%20conflicts%20and%2C%20at%20worst%2C%20the%20growth%20of%20these%20conflicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20practically%2C%20from%20a%20business%20perspective%2C%20I%20think%20one%20of%20the%20least%20talked-about%20business%20risks%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20face%20in%202024%20is%20rising%20attrition%20rates%20at%20companies.%20Right%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-job-great-resignation-big-stay-changing-jobs-market-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eattrition%20is%20at%20an%20all-time%20low%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20history%20is%20any%20pattern%2C%20attrition%20always%20catches%20up.%20Because%20right%20now%2C%20when%20the%20market's%20uncertain%2C%20people%20are%20holding%20on%20to%20their%20chairs.%20They%20really%20want%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-search-switch-harder-to-get-job-hiring-labor-market-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efeel%20stability%20in%20their%20professional%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20at%20some%20point%20they'll%20become%20more%20comfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20as%20the%20economy%20gets%20better%20companies%20will%20be%20at%20risk%20of%20seeing%20more%20and%20more%20of%20their%20people%20and%20top%20performers%20look%20for%20new%20opportunities%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20I'm%20worried%20that%20companies%20aren't%20spending%20enough%20time%20thinking%20about%2C%20right%20now%2C%20how%20their%20employees%20are%20doing%20and%20how%20do%20they%20make%20sure%20they're%20doing%20the%20things%20that%20will%20help%20their%20employees%20want%20to%20continue%20on%20the%20journey%20with%20them%20as%20the%20economy%20gets%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20one%20thing%20you%20got%20right%20in%202023%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20lucky%20enough%20to%20see%20some%20of%20the%20next-gen%20AI%20models%20by%20being%20part%20of%20Microsoft%20in%20the%20middle%20of%202022.%20And%20I%20think%20the%20big%20decision%20we%20made%20was%20to%20basically%20rewrite%20our%20road%20map%20and%20to%20say%20we're%20going%20to%20deploy%20AI%20across%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20capabilities%20on%20our%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20going%20to%20use%20it%20to%20help%20recruiters.%20We're%20going%20to%20use%20it%20to%20help%20salespeople.%20We're%20going%20to%20use%20it%20to%20help%20job%20seekers.%20We're%20going%20to%20use%20it%20to%20help%20people%20write%20their%20profiles%2C%20because%20people%20can%20be%20awkward%20about%20describing%20themselves%20professionally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20just%20saw%20so%20many%20different%20applications%20for%20this%20that%20the%20best%20thing%20we%20did%20was%20to%20realize%20this%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20time%20of%20massive%20experimentation%20to%20see%20where%20AI%20made%20the%20biggest%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20was%20one%20thing%20you%20got%20wrong%20in%202023%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20other%20companies%2C%20during%202021%20and%202022%20we%20saw%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20growth%20in%20our%20business.%20There%20were%20pockets%20where%20we%20overhired%2C%20and%20so%20we%20had%20a%20layoff%20earlier%20in%20the%20year%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20we%20were%20growing%20the%20business%20in%20a%20way%20that%20made%20sense%20given%20the%20economic%20environment.%20And%20that's%20hard%20on%20everyone%2C%20particularly%20the%20people%20impacted%20and%20all%20their%20friends%20and%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20think%20that%20it's%20an%20environment%20where%20finding%20energy%20in%20your%20day-to-day%20work%20is%20harder.%20Many%20people%20describe%20it%20as%20much%20more%20challenging%20than%20it%20used%20to%20be.%20And%20so%20I%20think%20that%20as%20a%20leadership%20team%2C%20bringing%20our%20attention%20to%20helping%20create%20energy%20for%20our%20teams%20has%20been%20something%20that%20I%20wish%20we%20acknowledged%20earlier%20in%20the%20year.%20I%20think%20we're%20doing%20great%20things%20about%20it%20now%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0getting%20people%20together%20more%20often%2C%20being%20more%20conscious%20of%20things%20that%20are%20tedious%20for%20our%20teams%2C%20trying%20to%20infuse%20more%20energy%20into%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20idea%20of%20energy%20being%20such%20an%20important%20thing%20for%20everyone%20to%20be%20at%20their%20best%20is%20something%20I%20wish%20I%20personally%20had%20seen%20more%20clearly%20earlier%20in%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-dan-shapero-interview-2024-outlook-amazed-by-ai-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702811581000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c833c50edbc52a864c721%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-dan-shapero-interview-2