0Western%20urban-industrial%20society%20that%20had%20sent%20emissaries%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20not%20changed.%20The%201967%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unoosa.org%2Foosa%2Fen%2Fourwork%2Fspacelaw%2Ftreaties%2Fouterspacetreaty.html%5C%22%3EOuter%20Space%20Treaty%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20space%20is%20the%20province%20of%20all%20humanity%2C%20but%20in%20reality%20it%E2%80%99s%20dominated%20by%20a%20few%20wealthy%20nations%20and%20individuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuxley%20said%20the%20notion%20of%20%E2%80%9Cstature%E2%80%9D%20assumed%20humans%20had%20a%20special%20and%20different%20status%20to%20other%20living%20beings.%20Given%20the%20immensity%20of%20space%2C%20talking%20of%20conquest%20was%2C%20in%20his%20opinion%2C%20%E2%80%9Ca%20trifle%20silly%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETillich%20was%20a%20theologian%20who%20fled%20Nazi%20Germany%20before%20the%20second%20world%20war.%20In%20his%20essay%2C%20he%20wrote%20about%20how%20seeing%20Earth%20from%20outside%20allowed%20us%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdemythologise%E2%80%9D%20our%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%20to%20the%20much-discussed%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FOverview_effect%5C%22%3Eoverview%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20inspires%20astronauts%20with%20a%20feeling%20of%20almost%20mystical%20awe%2C%20Tillich%20argued%20that%20the%20view%20from%20space%20made%20Earth%20a%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20material%20body%20to%20be%20looked%20at%20and%20considered%20as%20totally%20calculable%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F17121607%2Fimage-1613.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22792%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%