2Fquantum-physics%2F%5C%22%3Equantum%20mechanics%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20us%20a%20reality%20far%20beyond%20the%20ability%20of%20our%20senses%20to%20comprehend.%20Arendt%20said%20it%20was%20absurd%20to%20think%20such%20a%20cosmos%20could%20be%20%E2%80%9Cconquered%E2%80%9D.%20Instead%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20have%20come%20to%20our%20present%20capacity%20to%20%E2%80%98conquer%20space%E2%80%99%20through%20our%20new%20ability%20to%20handle%20nature%20from%20a%20point%20in%20the%20universe%20outside%20the%20earth%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20new%20geocentrism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20short%20human%20lifespan%20and%20the%20impossibility%20of%20moving%20faster%20than%20the%20speed%20of%20light%20mean%20humans%20are%20unlikely%20to%20travel%20beyond%20the%20Solar%20System.%20There%20is%20a%20limit%20to%20our%20current%20expansion%20into%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20that%20limit%20is%20reached%2C%20said%20Arendt%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20new%20world%20view%20that%20may%20conceivably%20grow%20out%20of%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20once%20more%20geocentric%20and%20anthropomorphic%2C%20although%20not%20in%20the%20old%20sense%20of%20the%20earth%20being%20the%20center%20of%20the%20universe%20and%20of%20man%20being%20the%20highest%20being%20there%20is.%E2%80%9D%20Humans%20would%20turn%20back%20to%20Earth%20to%20make%20meaning%20of%20their%20existence%2C%20and%20cease%20to%20dream%20of%20the%20stars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20new%20geocentrism%20may%20be%20exacerbated%20by%20an%20environmental%20problem%20already%20emerging%20from%20the%20rapid%20growth%20of%20satellite%20megaconstellations.%20The%20light%20they%20reflect%20is%20obscuring%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.discovermagazine.com%2Fenvironment%2Flight-pollution-threatens-millennia-old-indigenous-navigation-methods%5C%22%3Eview%20of%20the%20night%20sky%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20cutting%20our%20senses%20off%20from%20the%20larger%20cosmos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20far%20future%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20if%20it%20were%20technologically%20possible%20for%20humans%20to%20expand%20into%20the%20galaxy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArendt%20said%20assessing%20humanity%20from%20a%20position%20outside%20Earth%20would%20reduce%20the%20scale%20of%20human%20culture%20to%20the%20point%20at%20which%20humans%20would%20become%20like%20laboratory%20rats%2C%20studied%20as%20statistical%20patterns.%20From%20far%20enough%20away%2C%20all%20human%20culture%20would%20appear%20as%20nothing%20more%20than%20a%20%E2%80%9Clarge%20scale%20biological%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArendt%20did%20not%20see%20this%20as%20an%20increase%20in%20stature%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conquest%20of%20space%20and%20the%20science%20that%20made%20it%20possible%20have%20come%20perilously%20close%20to%20this%20point%20%5Bof%20seeing%20human%20culture%20as%20a%20biological%20process%5D.%20If%20they%20ever%20should%20reach%20it%20in%20earnest%2C%20the%20stature%20of%20man%20would%20not%20simply%20be%20lowered%20by%20all%20standards%20we%20know%20of%2C%20but%20have%20been%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESixty%20years%20on%2C%20nations%20are%20competing%20to%20exploit%20lunar%20and%20asteroid%20mineral%20resources.%20Private%20corporations%20and%20space%20billionaires%20are%20increasingly%20being%20touted%20as%20the%20way%20forward.%20After%20the%20Moon%2C%20Mars%20is%20the%20next%20world%20in%20line%20for%20%E2%80%9Cconquest%E2%80%9D.%20The%20contemporary%20movement%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faeon.co%2Fessays%2Fwhy-longtermism-is-the-worlds-most-dangerous-secular-credo%5C%22%3Elongtermism%3C%2Fa%3E%20promotes%20living%20on%20other%20planets%20as%20insurance%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FGlobal_catastrophic_risk%5C%22%3Eexistential%20risk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20a%20far%20future%20where%20humans%20(or%20some%20form%20of%20them)%20spread%20to%20fill%20the%20galaxies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20question%20remains.%20Is%20space%20travel%20enhancing%20what%20we%20value%20about%20humanity%3F%20Arendt%20and%20her%20fellow%20essayists%20were%20not%20convinced.%20For%20me%2C%20the%20answer%20will%20depend%20on%20what%20values%20we%20choose%20to%20prioritise%20in%20this%20new%20era%20of%20interplanetary%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20developed%20from%20a%20panel%20discussion%20at%20the%20Wheeler%20Centre.%20You%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Flisten%2Fprograms%2Fbigideas%2Fspace-race-travel-humanity-ethics-hannah-arrendt-science%2F102961384%5C%22%3Elisten%20to%20it%20here%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F218235%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Falice-gorman-4234%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAlice%20Gorman%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20Associate%20Professor%20in%20Archaeology%20and%20Space%20Studies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fflinders-university-972%5C%22%3EFlinders%20University%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwas-going-to-space-a-good-idea-218235%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702800042000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F17124747%2Fimage-1614.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fwas-going-to-space-a-good-idea%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22After%20the%20Moon%2C%20Mars