e%208%20such%20bills.%20One%20bill%20was%20assented%20to%2C%207%20were%20referred%20to%20the%20President%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%20Justice%20Nariman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20he%20is%20looking%20forward%20to%20a%20day%20when%20only%20independent%20persons%20will%20be%20favoured%20for%20these%20roles%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20waiting%20for%20the%20day%20when%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20lay%20down%20that%20%E2%80%98look%2C%20it%20is%20only%20independent%20functionaries%20who%20are%20supposed%20to%20fill%20these%20great%20offices.%20Not%20the%20kind%20of%20people%20that%20we%20find%20today%2C%20like%20in%20Kerala%2C%20where%20wholesale%2C%20after%20you%20slept%20over%20the%20bills%2C%20you%20just%20give%20them%20back%20to%20the%20President.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nariman%E2%80%99s%20highlighting%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Article%20370%20judgment%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20it%20upheld%20the%20constitutional%20order%20that%20read%20down%20the%20article%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0was%20most%20scathing.%20He%20said%20it%20had%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctremendous%20impact%20on%20federalism.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20noted%20that%20there%20was%20a%20key%20intent%20behind%20bifurcating%20the%20state%20when%20there%20was%20already%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%20imposted%20%E2%80%93%20to%20bypass%20the%20clause%20in%20Article%20356%20which%20says%20that%20such%20a%20rule%20cannot%20exceed%20one%20year%20unless%20there%20is%20a%20national%20emergency%20or%20the%20Election%20Commission%20says%20that%20elections%20are%20not%20possible%20to%20be%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20if%20a%20state%20government%20is%20unable%20to%20function%20according%20to%20constitutional%20provisions%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20can%20take%20direct%20control%20of%20the%20state%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Nariman%20called%20the%20solution%20found%20by%20the%20government%20%E2%80%9Cingenious%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20he%20criticised%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20for%20skipping%20this%20key%20question%20in%20its%20decision%2C%20based%20on%20an%20undertaking%20given%20by%20the%20Solicitor%20General%20that%20statehood%20will%20be%20restored.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Solicitor%20General%20does%20not%20have%20any%20authority%20to%20bind%20the%20successor%20government%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20noted%2C%20citing%20his%20own%20disavowal%20of%20such%20a%20statement%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EShreya%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ESinghal%3C%2Fem%3E%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20also%20criticised%20the%20%E2%80%9Cnearly%20four%20years%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20decision%20took%20to%20arrive%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20move%20took%20place%20in%202019%2C%20which%20is%20when%20the%20petitions%20were%20filed%20and%20that%20there%20has%20been%20no%20democratically%20elected%20government%20in%20the%20region%20for%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FLg4VHsnU1aw%3Fsi%3DzO4gz049Tfd6ISJg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702718312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F16144643%2FUntitled-design-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fjustice-nariman-speech-election-commission-article-370-supreme-court-bbc-media%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Delivering%20the%20Smt%20Bansari%20Sheth%20Endowment%20Lecture%2C%20the%20judge%20noted%20that%20four%20%26quot%3Bmost%20disturbing%26quot%3B%20things%20have%20happened%20in%20the%20country%20this%20year%20itself.%C2%A0He%20also%20was%20severely%